WEBVTT

00:01.035 --> 00:03.106
Previously onPromised Land...

00:03.210 --> 00:04.970
-Hello, Carmen.
-Mom?

00:05.039 --> 00:06.282
I haven't seen you
since you were...

00:06.385 --> 00:07.662
16, I think?

00:07.731 --> 00:08.974
JOE: Margaret Honeycroft

00:09.043 --> 00:11.804
has launched a hostile
takeover of my company.

00:11.873 --> 00:13.737
I want you to follow
my husband.

00:20.813 --> 00:21.883
Okay?

00:23.230 --> 00:24.576
JOE: Lettie?

00:27.406 --> 00:28.373
Billy.

00:28.442 --> 00:30.064
Hello, brother.

00:30.892 --> 00:36.381
♪♪

00:36.450 --> 00:42.042
♪♪

00:42.111 --> 00:44.423
How long you been back?

00:44.527 --> 00:46.425
Joe, please...

00:46.494 --> 00:48.945
Wait, wait.
You guys know each other?

00:49.049 --> 00:49.911
Joe.

00:50.015 --> 00:51.879
It's a very simple
question.

00:51.948 --> 00:53.915
I was going to reach out, but --

00:54.019 --> 00:55.848
How long?

00:55.917 --> 00:56.918
I-I-I told him
not to tell you, Joe.

00:57.022 --> 00:58.058
It's my fault.

00:58.127 --> 01:00.163
How...long?

01:00.267 --> 01:01.716
About a month.

01:01.785 --> 01:03.477
-No, Joe!
-Dad!

01:06.480 --> 01:08.240
No, he's been helping
with Junior.

01:08.309 --> 01:09.621
We've been talking.
That's it.

01:09.724 --> 01:11.416
Doesn't look like it.

01:11.485 --> 01:13.728
JUNIOR: Wait, can somebody tell
me what the hell is going on?

01:13.797 --> 01:15.730
JOE: We're going home.
Get in the car.

01:15.799 --> 01:17.767
Can we just take a moment,
please?

01:17.870 --> 01:20.114
I wasn't talking to you.

01:21.288 --> 01:24.187
♪♪

01:24.291 --> 01:31.815
♪♪

01:31.919 --> 01:39.582
♪♪

01:59.636 --> 02:01.362
[speaks Spanish]

02:02.674 --> 02:04.089
[radio static crackles]

02:04.158 --> 02:07.299
["Te Lo Pido Por Favor" plays]

02:19.932 --> 02:22.763
♪ Necesito Lettie♪

02:22.832 --> 02:27.388
♪♪

02:38.192 --> 02:45.889
♪♪

02:45.993 --> 02:47.512
-MICHAEL: Hey.
-VERONICA: Hi.

02:47.581 --> 02:49.997
Sorry this is so last minute.
Come on, baby.

02:50.066 --> 02:51.585
-It's okay.
-Ooh.

02:51.688 --> 02:52.620
-I'm gonna miss you guys.
-[smooches]

02:52.724 --> 02:54.519
Oh, we're gonna miss you, too,
right?

02:57.038 --> 02:58.281
Yeah? How long are you
in San Francisco?

02:58.385 --> 02:59.420
Uh, couple nights.

02:59.524 --> 03:01.629
Okay, well, good luck,
drive safe,

03:01.733 --> 03:03.010
and make lots of money.

03:04.356 --> 03:05.254
What's that
supposed to mean?

03:05.357 --> 03:07.566
Nothing.
It doesn't mean anything.

03:07.635 --> 03:09.810
Well, you said it,
so it must mean something.

03:09.879 --> 03:11.708
[sighs] No, Michael.

03:11.777 --> 03:13.400
It's about that 50 grand,
isn't it?

03:14.849 --> 03:15.850
No.

03:15.919 --> 03:17.231
Just...good luck
in your meetings.

03:17.300 --> 03:19.647
Thanks. And don't worry.

03:19.751 --> 03:21.580
I'll try not to spend
any "unauthorized funds."

03:21.684 --> 03:22.823
[car door closes]

03:22.892 --> 03:24.031
I love you, too.

03:24.100 --> 03:25.205
[engine starts]

03:32.281 --> 03:34.904
Hi. He just left.

03:35.007 --> 03:37.113
[engine revs]

03:38.873 --> 03:40.427
-CRUZ: I see him.
-Yeah.

03:40.496 --> 03:42.498
Let me know where he goes
and what he does,

03:42.601 --> 03:44.879
and call me when you get to
San Francisco.

03:44.948 --> 03:50.885
♪♪

03:50.954 --> 03:53.336
Yo. So then everything
goes dead quiet,

03:53.440 --> 03:57.029
like dead quiet,
and Dad's like, "How long?"

03:57.098 --> 03:59.100
-How long what?
-Are you ready for this?

03:59.169 --> 04:00.930
The priest that I've been
coaching soccer with?

04:01.033 --> 04:02.069
He's Dad's brother.

04:02.138 --> 04:03.208
-What?
-What?

04:03.277 --> 04:04.209
-Mm-hmm.
-Wait, wait, wait.

04:04.278 --> 04:05.486
Father Ramos is Uncle Billy?

04:05.590 --> 04:06.901
-Mateo's dad?
-Yep.

04:06.970 --> 04:08.593
I thought he was, like,
some druggie loser guy.

04:08.662 --> 04:10.250
I guess he found God
and came back here.

04:10.319 --> 04:11.906
And Lettie knew about this
but didn't tell Papá?

04:11.975 --> 04:14.426
-And what'd Papi do?
-So, then Dad --

04:14.495 --> 04:16.532
boom -- clocks him in the face.

04:16.635 --> 04:18.741
-He punched a priest?
-In the middle of the church.

04:18.810 --> 04:20.225
-What?
-Mm-hmm.

04:20.294 --> 04:21.261
No, no, no, no.

04:21.330 --> 04:24.540
So, I see
you heard the news.

04:24.643 --> 04:26.231
Thought the secret
was out, so...

04:26.300 --> 04:27.784
How are you?
Are you okay?

04:27.888 --> 04:29.096
Yeah, I'm fine.

04:29.165 --> 04:30.822
I mean, I could use a map
to make sense of this family.

04:30.925 --> 04:32.893
[chuckles]
We're so messed up.

04:32.962 --> 04:34.308
Wait.

04:34.377 --> 04:36.724
So, should I invite Uncle Billy
to my birthday party?

04:36.828 --> 04:39.313
You think that's funny?

04:40.487 --> 04:43.662
Get off of my counter, Carmen.

04:43.731 --> 04:46.113
-Whoo!
-What did I do?

04:46.182 --> 04:53.948
♪♪

04:54.017 --> 04:56.848
[swishes wine]

04:59.678 --> 05:00.955
That good, huh?

05:01.024 --> 05:04.062
Haskins left me 10 barrels of
juice from his last vintage.

05:04.165 --> 05:05.512
If I can't blend
something decent out of it,

05:05.581 --> 05:07.030
I'm not gonna be able
to make rent.

05:07.962 --> 05:09.309
What are you up to?

05:10.379 --> 05:11.897
I wanted to ask,

05:12.001 --> 05:14.210
do you have a pair of shoelaces
I could borrow?

05:14.314 --> 05:16.385
I don't think shoelaces
are gonna save those.

05:16.454 --> 05:21.321
My mother gave me these before
I left for the long walk.

05:21.390 --> 05:23.840
She saved for years
to send me here.

05:23.944 --> 05:25.290
Oh. Right.

05:26.395 --> 05:28.293
N-No, you should definitely
keep them.

05:31.503 --> 05:34.023
It's hard to be away
from my family.

05:35.024 --> 05:36.439
You're lucky.

05:36.543 --> 05:38.959
You have your mom and your uncle
and your cousins

05:39.028 --> 05:40.857
just a half-mile up the hill.

05:40.926 --> 05:43.032
I guess it just seems
a little farther than that.

05:43.101 --> 05:47.139
Well, you could be closer to
them if you wanted to, no?

05:47.208 --> 05:48.175
They're Joe's kids.

05:48.244 --> 05:50.039
They're the ones
who don't want it.

05:53.042 --> 05:55.009
Mamá?
What are you doing here?

05:55.078 --> 05:58.599
Um...he's back.

06:01.050 --> 06:02.051
My father?

06:02.154 --> 06:04.433
♪♪

06:04.536 --> 06:06.711
I didn't care that
Taste of Sonoma went

06:06.780 --> 06:08.333
to the Ritz,
but it killed me that they

06:08.402 --> 06:10.370
didn't see your design.

06:10.439 --> 06:12.924
Thought the least I could do
was invite you to ride with me.

06:13.027 --> 06:14.822
-Beautiful horses.
-Mm.

06:14.926 --> 06:16.652
And at least
you showed faith in me.

06:16.755 --> 06:19.171
Anyway, I'm over it.

06:19.240 --> 06:20.449
Maybe you shouldn't be.

06:20.552 --> 06:21.898
Maybe you should
tell your father

06:21.967 --> 06:23.797
to stop taking you
for granted.

06:23.900 --> 06:25.626
Well, not the best timing.

06:25.730 --> 06:28.180
He's got other drama
to deal with.

06:28.249 --> 06:29.630
You know Uncle Billy?

06:29.734 --> 06:31.080
What am I saying?
Of course you do.

06:31.183 --> 06:32.081
Mm-hmm.

06:32.184 --> 06:34.394
Well, he's back.

06:35.291 --> 06:36.292
What?

06:36.396 --> 06:37.949
Yeah.
And get this --

06:38.052 --> 06:39.813
he's a priest.

06:39.916 --> 06:41.849
Apparently, he and Lettie
have been having lunch

06:41.953 --> 06:43.644
and she didn't tell my dad,
so...

06:43.748 --> 06:45.784
[exhales sharply] Boy.

06:45.888 --> 06:47.372
Lettie and Billy.

06:48.580 --> 06:50.064
I'm not gonna stand here
and tell you

06:50.133 --> 06:51.583
that Lettie doesn't love
your father.

06:51.652 --> 06:52.964
They've been married
for 20 years.

06:53.067 --> 06:55.069
But Billy?

06:55.138 --> 06:57.831
Billy turned her head
like no one else.

06:57.934 --> 07:00.454
Oh, your father must be
fit to be tied.

07:00.523 --> 07:02.491
Oh, and all in time
for your birthday.

07:02.594 --> 07:04.493
You remembered.

07:04.596 --> 07:06.805
[chuckles]
Carmen, I was there.

07:06.909 --> 07:08.945
[both laugh]

07:09.014 --> 07:10.119
And what have you
got planned?

07:10.222 --> 07:11.914
Mm, I'm throwing myself
a party.

07:11.983 --> 07:13.191
It is your 25th.

07:13.294 --> 07:15.504
Oh, yeah. I've been planning it
for weeks.

07:15.607 --> 07:17.506
-Tons of cool artists.
-Mm.

07:17.609 --> 07:19.542
And I've got
a special drink planned,

07:19.646 --> 07:21.268
maybe a musical guest.

07:21.337 --> 07:22.614
Oh, that sounds
incredible.

07:24.720 --> 07:26.135
Do you --

07:26.238 --> 07:27.274
Do you want to come?

07:29.000 --> 07:30.657
I probably shouldn't.

07:30.726 --> 07:33.142
No. Please, come.

07:33.245 --> 07:35.972
Oh...Carmen, it's okay.

07:36.041 --> 07:37.526
Uh, Joe and Lettie
have enough drama.

07:37.629 --> 07:41.461
I want you to come.
You're my mom.

07:43.463 --> 07:45.810
I did miss
the last 22 of these, so...

07:46.638 --> 07:49.123
It would be nice
to be there for this one.

07:49.192 --> 07:51.816
Then it's settled.

07:51.885 --> 07:53.542
You're coming.

07:57.753 --> 07:59.479
[police siren chirps]

08:00.341 --> 08:02.205
-¿Qué?
-[speaks Spanish]

08:04.173 --> 08:05.312
-[police siren wailing]
-[sighs]

08:15.460 --> 08:16.496
¿Como?

08:18.014 --> 08:22.191
♪♪

08:24.745 --> 08:26.713
Jose.

08:27.507 --> 08:28.922
Leticia.

08:30.164 --> 08:31.338
Guillermo.

08:31.407 --> 08:32.339
I go by Billy.

08:32.408 --> 08:34.514
I bet you do.

08:34.583 --> 08:36.377
We work on a vineyard.

08:36.481 --> 08:37.482
Heritage House, in Sonoma?

08:37.551 --> 08:39.380
Sonoma's the other direction.

08:39.484 --> 08:41.486
A machine broke.

08:41.555 --> 08:44.178
Our boss sent us to Bakersfield
for a new part.

08:44.247 --> 08:45.697
This is his truck.

08:47.527 --> 08:51.531
Well, [sighs]
you got no registration.

08:51.600 --> 08:53.878
Which means
I gotta take you in.

08:53.947 --> 08:55.707
After I search the vehicle.

08:55.776 --> 08:56.881
Well, I...

08:57.813 --> 08:59.228
JOSE: Wait.

08:59.331 --> 09:03.888
Señor.
I found the registration.

09:03.957 --> 09:09.549
♪♪

09:11.551 --> 09:18.558
♪♪

09:18.627 --> 09:20.767
The hell are three Mexicans
doing with $1,000?

09:20.836 --> 09:22.113
It's for the machine part --

09:22.216 --> 09:23.424
Was I talking to you?

09:23.528 --> 09:25.288
Billy, calma.

09:27.290 --> 09:28.395
This your boss's money?

09:28.464 --> 09:31.087
Yes.

09:31.156 --> 09:35.782
But of course, it's better
to go back with no part

09:35.851 --> 09:38.819
than to go to jail,
no, señor?

09:38.923 --> 09:41.442
Smart choice.

09:41.546 --> 09:42.996
Now, why don't you buenos tardes

09:43.099 --> 09:44.722
and get the hell
out of my county?

09:47.483 --> 09:48.657
[car door closes,
engine starts]

09:48.760 --> 09:50.106
"Buenos tardes."

09:50.210 --> 09:58.977
♪♪

09:59.081 --> 10:01.255
[laughs]

10:15.718 --> 10:16.823
For the business.

10:16.892 --> 10:18.652
Ah. For the business.

10:24.624 --> 10:27.143
Hey.

10:27.212 --> 10:29.111
You were supposed to call me
when you got to San Francisco.

10:29.180 --> 10:30.526
Five hours ago.

10:30.630 --> 10:32.321
I'm not in San Francisco.

10:32.424 --> 10:34.288
I'm at some mansion in LA.

10:34.357 --> 10:35.704
And Michael's there?

10:35.807 --> 10:37.291
Inside.

10:37.360 --> 10:38.707
It's some kind of party.

10:40.053 --> 10:41.399
Well, can you get in?

10:41.502 --> 10:44.851
I'm a little too brown
for this crowd.

10:44.920 --> 10:46.266
Lots of money here.

10:46.335 --> 10:47.854
Okay, text me the address.

10:47.923 --> 10:49.752
-Take some photos.
-[cellphone beeps]

10:49.856 --> 10:51.858
Have a great day.

10:51.927 --> 10:53.618
YOUNG WOMAN: He's really sweet,
right? He's really nice.

10:53.687 --> 10:57.035
[indistinct conversations]

11:02.558 --> 11:03.973
Mateo.

11:04.905 --> 11:05.906
Look at you.

11:06.010 --> 11:07.908
Me?

11:08.909 --> 11:10.842
Look at you.
You're a priest.

11:10.911 --> 11:12.464
I am.

11:12.533 --> 11:14.052
Lettie gave me your number.

11:14.121 --> 11:16.330
I start to dial it every day,
and I just...

11:16.399 --> 11:18.056
It's fine.

11:19.333 --> 11:20.300
We're here now.

11:20.369 --> 11:21.335
Yes, we are.

11:21.404 --> 11:23.337
[chuckles]

11:29.343 --> 11:30.517
I hear you're a winemaker.

11:30.586 --> 11:33.347
Yeah, trying to be.
Trying to be.

11:33.416 --> 11:34.728
Probably not as good
as you would have been.

11:34.797 --> 11:37.386
No, I was better at drinking
the wine than making it.

11:37.489 --> 11:38.767
[chuckles]

11:38.870 --> 11:40.492
You're -- You're sober now,
though, right?

11:40.561 --> 11:42.529
Going on 10 years.

11:42.598 --> 11:44.393
It's crazy, you getting assigned
to Sonoma.

11:45.912 --> 11:49.709
Maybe it's the Lord's way
of rewarding me.

11:49.778 --> 11:51.745
There's so much
I want to ask you.

11:51.814 --> 11:53.920
I know. I'm sure.

11:53.989 --> 11:55.542
Maybe we can get a --

11:55.611 --> 11:57.164
We can get
whatever you want.

11:57.268 --> 11:58.441
Or, you know what?
Why don't we get dinner?

11:58.545 --> 11:59.788
I'm buddies with the chef
at Che Fico. We can talk.

11:59.891 --> 12:00.823
It'll be the best meal
of your life.

12:00.927 --> 12:02.687
Mateo.

12:02.756 --> 12:05.414
That all sounds wonderful.

12:05.483 --> 12:08.797
But maybe we should take it
one step at a time.

12:09.901 --> 12:12.283
This is a big change
for both of us.

12:12.386 --> 12:15.286
That where he hit you?

12:15.389 --> 12:18.013
It was a big shock.

12:18.116 --> 12:19.773
Your mother and I
could've handled it better.

12:19.842 --> 12:21.741
You could've
handled it better?

12:21.810 --> 12:23.984
Joe had every right
to be angry.

12:24.088 --> 12:25.296
Oh, it's just like him --

12:25.399 --> 12:26.746
lashing out at
whatever he can't control.

12:26.815 --> 12:28.471
Mateo.

12:28.575 --> 12:30.163
I left you.

12:30.266 --> 12:32.786
-I know, but --
-No. No "but."

12:32.855 --> 12:34.788
I made a terrible mistake.

12:34.857 --> 12:37.170
And? I forgive you.
I forgave you a long time ago.

12:37.273 --> 12:39.344
Why?

12:39.448 --> 12:41.381
I've done nothing
to earn that forgiveness.

12:42.969 --> 12:44.004
No, I guess you haven't.

12:44.108 --> 12:45.972
You haven't done
a damn thing to earn it.

12:46.041 --> 12:47.663
Mateo, wait.

12:49.285 --> 12:51.253
I'm just saying,
we have time.

12:53.117 --> 12:55.291
I'd like the chance to
deserve your forgiveness.

12:55.395 --> 12:57.155
Yeah. Sure.

12:57.224 --> 12:59.433
We-- We'll take it slow.

13:05.474 --> 13:07.372
Joe, we need to talk.

13:07.476 --> 13:10.030
Can you make sure the pool guy
comes on Friday?

13:10.134 --> 13:12.170
I want it cleaned
before Carmen's party.

13:12.239 --> 13:13.758
LETTIE: Yes, of course.

13:13.827 --> 13:14.863
Joe.

13:14.966 --> 13:16.899
There's nothing to talk about.

13:17.003 --> 13:19.488
You say you and Billy
have only been talking,

13:19.557 --> 13:22.353
you say he's been
a good influence on Junior.

13:22.456 --> 13:25.183
I guess the lying, doping drunk
who abandoned you

13:25.252 --> 13:27.289
is a better influence on our son
than I am.

13:27.358 --> 13:28.704
Mysterious ways, huh?

13:28.808 --> 13:30.050
Don't do this.

13:30.154 --> 13:31.500
Do what? What am I doing?

13:31.603 --> 13:33.536
You're hurting.

13:33.640 --> 13:35.090
And instead of
talking to me about it,

13:35.193 --> 13:36.367
you're just shutting me out.

13:36.470 --> 13:39.335
At least...let me apologize.

13:40.854 --> 13:42.373
Apology accepted.

13:42.476 --> 13:43.995
Damn it, Joe.

13:45.652 --> 13:47.412
You know I love you.

13:47.516 --> 13:49.863
I've got a bunch of
yield reports to get through.

13:49.932 --> 13:53.004
What happened between
me and Billy --

13:53.073 --> 13:55.869
that was over years ago.

13:55.938 --> 13:57.560
It's always been you.

13:58.561 --> 13:59.839
Talk to me.

14:00.874 --> 14:02.462
Let me in.

14:08.226 --> 14:09.814
[sighs]

14:12.230 --> 14:14.957
[brakes screech]

14:15.061 --> 14:16.890
[engine shuts off]

14:38.912 --> 14:39.913
iAy!

14:41.052 --> 14:43.054
[train horn blares
in distance]

14:45.125 --> 14:46.851
[knock on door]

14:56.274 --> 14:57.793
[speaks Spanish]

15:07.078 --> 15:08.286
Hey.

15:18.952 --> 15:20.540
-Rosa!
-Juana!

15:23.301 --> 15:26.132
Juana! Juana!

15:26.201 --> 15:27.478
Juana!

15:34.623 --> 15:39.283
♪♪

15:44.805 --> 15:46.738
Juana! Juana!

16:14.939 --> 16:16.216
Leticia, no!

16:36.029 --> 16:37.962
[speaks Spanish]

16:43.002 --> 16:45.452
You really think
he's a priest?

16:45.556 --> 16:47.420
Yeah, I have no idea.

16:47.523 --> 16:48.973
What I do know is that
Mateo must be freaking,

16:49.042 --> 16:50.492
and that dress has back.

16:50.561 --> 16:52.459
It's not too much back?

16:52.563 --> 16:54.427
Is water too wet? What kind
of a question is that?

16:54.530 --> 16:57.430
Either of you guys talked
to him lately? Mateo?

16:57.533 --> 16:59.432
-Mnh.
-No, I haven't.

16:59.535 --> 17:00.985
I want to reach out.

17:01.054 --> 17:02.573
God knows what he must be
thinking right now.

17:02.676 --> 17:04.540
He doesn't come to me
with that kind of stuff.

17:04.644 --> 17:06.059
I love it.

17:06.128 --> 17:07.302
I love all of them,
actually.

17:07.405 --> 17:09.856
Oh. Ms. Honeycroft
has excellent taste.

17:09.925 --> 17:12.065
What does "Ms. Honeycroft"
have to do with it?

17:13.239 --> 17:15.379
Uh, it was her idea.

17:15.448 --> 17:16.932
I thought you were
planning the party.

17:17.036 --> 17:18.071
I am.

17:18.140 --> 17:20.763
It's just, she knows
a lot of amazing vendors,

17:20.867 --> 17:24.664
and, uh, she felt bad, V.

17:24.733 --> 17:26.010
How could I say no?

17:26.079 --> 17:28.909
Easy. Watch. No.

17:31.291 --> 17:33.086
Carmen, you didn't invite her,
did you?

17:35.882 --> 17:37.780
[exhales sharply]

17:38.885 --> 17:41.163
Are you and Margaret,
like, a thing now?

17:41.267 --> 17:42.475
I'm sorry, Mami.

17:42.578 --> 17:44.925
I was gonna tell you.
I hope that it's okay.

17:45.029 --> 17:46.341
Oh, no, it's your birthday.

17:46.444 --> 17:48.032
You can invite whoever you want.

17:48.101 --> 17:49.413
See?

17:49.482 --> 17:52.830
Mami doesn't have a problem
with it. Why should you?

17:52.933 --> 17:55.039
Oh, I don't know.
Maybe because she abandoned us?

17:55.108 --> 17:57.731
Oh, she didn't abandon us
by the roadside, V.

17:57.800 --> 17:59.664
-You're being dramatic.
-Am I?

17:59.768 --> 18:00.976
Yeah,
it was more like poolside.

18:01.080 --> 18:03.772
[chuckles] No offense, Carmen,

18:03.841 --> 18:05.325
but you don't know
what you're talking about.

18:05.429 --> 18:07.465
You were, what,
2 when she left?

18:07.534 --> 18:09.709
You don't know what it's like
to have a mom one moment

18:09.778 --> 18:10.882
and an empty space the next.

18:10.951 --> 18:12.919
"An empty space"?

18:12.988 --> 18:14.783
Lettie, you're the best thing

18:14.852 --> 18:16.509
that ever happened
to this family.

18:16.612 --> 18:17.613
But just because you were here

18:17.682 --> 18:19.960
doesn't let Margaret
off the hook.

18:20.064 --> 18:21.134
All right, I was there
when Mom left,

18:21.203 --> 18:22.446
and I'm still going
to the party.

18:22.515 --> 18:25.138
-Yeah, well, that's you.
-Hey, whoa, whoa, V.

18:25.207 --> 18:26.622
You're coming to my party.

18:26.691 --> 18:29.142
You're my only sister.
You have to be there.

18:29.211 --> 18:30.971
[scoffs]

18:31.075 --> 18:33.595
No, no, no, no, no.
Niñas. [speaks Spanish]

18:34.665 --> 18:36.115
[speaks Spanish]

18:38.289 --> 18:39.566
I figured you'd be
hiding up here.

18:39.670 --> 18:40.705
JOE: It's called working.

18:40.809 --> 18:42.707
Need these tanks cleaned
before harvest.

18:42.811 --> 18:44.537
Don't you have your own winery
to run?

18:44.640 --> 18:47.678
I saw what you did.
Big man punching a priest.

18:47.781 --> 18:49.887
I hit a guy sneaking around
with my wife.

18:49.990 --> 18:52.303
I don't care what costume
he was wearing.

18:52.372 --> 18:54.823
What'd you say to him?
You tell him to steer clear?

18:54.892 --> 18:57.515
I swear to God, if you mess this
up for me, Joe...

18:57.619 --> 18:59.966
Mess what up?

19:00.035 --> 19:03.797
Big reunion with
the man who left you?

19:03.866 --> 19:06.214
He's been in town
for months, Mateo.

19:06.317 --> 19:08.492
Why hasn't he
reached out to you?

19:08.561 --> 19:10.528
Hmm?

19:12.599 --> 19:14.498
Look, you don't know him
like I do.

19:14.567 --> 19:16.879
You have no idea how dangerous
my brother coming

19:16.983 --> 19:18.157
back here could be.

19:18.226 --> 19:19.399
For all of us.

19:19.503 --> 19:20.987
Oh, and why is that?

19:21.056 --> 19:22.195
What, you afraid
he's gonna blow up

19:22.264 --> 19:24.024
this perfect little life
you've built?

19:24.128 --> 19:26.165
Remind you
who you really are?

19:28.581 --> 19:29.858
Who I am?

19:30.893 --> 19:34.690
I'm the guy who has given you
every opportunity.

19:34.759 --> 19:38.073
I'm the guy who never once
lied to you or your mother.

19:38.177 --> 19:39.937
Your father?

19:40.040 --> 19:42.629
He's the one who went out
for cigarettes when you were 10,

19:42.733 --> 19:46.012
and the next time you saw him
was today.

19:46.081 --> 19:48.187
So, ask yourself --
which one of us

19:48.256 --> 19:50.050
has more to be ashamed of?

19:50.154 --> 19:52.570
He's gonna prove you wrong
this time.

19:52.639 --> 19:55.021
People don't change, Mateo.

19:55.090 --> 19:56.816
Only their lies do.

19:56.885 --> 19:59.163
[flashlight clicks]

20:02.718 --> 20:04.686
[speaking Spanish]

20:04.755 --> 20:06.550
iAy!, Rosa.

20:06.619 --> 20:08.103
[door closes]

20:08.207 --> 20:11.382
[inhales shakily]

20:11.451 --> 20:13.212
-[sighs]
-[sniffles]

20:34.716 --> 20:36.200
iOye!

20:47.798 --> 20:50.076
iAy!, Rosa.

21:20.658 --> 21:22.522
Hey.

21:39.021 --> 21:42.301
[Pink Slip's "Dulce" plays]

21:42.370 --> 21:44.268
For party favors,
Ms. Honeycroft was thinking

21:44.337 --> 21:45.856
earrings for the ladies...

21:45.959 --> 21:47.547
CARMEN: Ooh.

21:47.651 --> 21:48.962
...cufflinks
for the gentlemen.

21:49.031 --> 21:50.101
♪ Dulce y dulce,
sweeter than sweet♪

21:50.170 --> 21:52.034
♪ Ay, señorita...♪

21:52.138 --> 21:53.933
Carmen, this is
quite an expense.

21:54.002 --> 21:55.210
Uh, well...

21:55.314 --> 21:56.694
It's all right, ma'am.

21:56.763 --> 21:58.040
Ms. Honeycroft is covering it.

21:58.144 --> 21:59.628
W-We're splitting it.

21:59.697 --> 22:00.905
Ma.

22:01.009 --> 22:02.321
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

22:02.390 --> 22:04.288
So sorry I'm a little late.
I see you've met Justine.

22:04.357 --> 22:05.565
-Hello, baby.
-Hi.

22:05.669 --> 22:07.429
Mm.

22:07.533 --> 22:09.017
And Antonio, sweetheart,
how are you?

22:09.120 --> 22:10.156
-Good.
-[smooches]

22:10.225 --> 22:12.400
Glad to see you
getting reacquainted.

22:12.503 --> 22:14.125
Oh, it's been such a blessing

22:14.194 --> 22:15.230
getting to know
these two better.

22:15.334 --> 22:16.990
And how are you, Lettie?

22:17.059 --> 22:18.716
I heard
Billy's back in town.

22:18.820 --> 22:21.892
That's exciting.

22:21.995 --> 22:25.723
♪♪

22:25.792 --> 22:27.000
DANIELA: You're going
to pass out

22:27.069 --> 22:28.830
if you don't drink something.

22:28.899 --> 22:30.728
[panting]

22:30.832 --> 22:32.178
Veronica called.

22:32.247 --> 22:33.179
I saw.

22:33.248 --> 22:34.594
She's been texting me.

22:34.698 --> 22:36.044
I'm sure she just wants
to talk about Father Ramos.

22:36.147 --> 22:38.874
Is that a bad thing?

22:38.943 --> 22:42.602
I know it's hard
with your father, with Joe,

22:42.706 --> 22:45.433
but maybe you're making it
harder than it needs to be.

22:45.536 --> 22:47.918
I just mean sometimes
you can't make things

22:48.021 --> 22:51.162
what you want them to be,
when you want them to be.

22:51.231 --> 22:53.924
You have to let them
come to you.

22:54.027 --> 22:56.305
Especially
the good things.

22:56.409 --> 22:58.411
It's kinda scary how you can
see right through me.

22:58.480 --> 22:59.930
Does that make you nervous?

23:00.033 --> 23:01.172
Terrified.

23:01.241 --> 23:04.383
I think I like being scary.

23:08.732 --> 23:12.252
-Junior. Everything okay?
-Yeah. Yeah.

23:12.356 --> 23:13.668
Why -- Why -- Why do you ask?

23:13.771 --> 23:14.910
MATEO: 'Cause I don't think
you've ever been

23:15.014 --> 23:16.395
to my house before.

23:17.913 --> 23:20.122
It's, uh...It's nice.

23:20.226 --> 23:22.366
This about Father Ramos?

23:23.609 --> 23:24.748
I'll let you guys talk.

23:27.302 --> 23:28.648
Mom said he's been helping you.

23:28.752 --> 23:30.961
It's weird. I feel closer to him
than I do to Dad.

23:31.064 --> 23:33.412
And when Joe hit him, I...

23:33.481 --> 23:35.448
all I could think about
was kicking my dad's ass.

23:35.517 --> 23:36.932
I figured you could relate.

23:37.001 --> 23:40.384
I definitely wanted to kick
your dad's ass more than once.

23:40.453 --> 23:41.834
[chuckles]

23:43.698 --> 23:45.803
[keyboard clacking]

23:48.875 --> 23:51.602
[computer chimes]

23:51.671 --> 23:58.229
♪♪

23:58.298 --> 24:00.542
[laughter]

24:00.646 --> 24:03.545
-Thank you.
-[giggles]

24:03.649 --> 24:12.140
♪♪

24:12.243 --> 24:16.109
[footsteps approaching]

24:16.178 --> 24:17.525
Hey. You got a sec?

24:17.628 --> 24:20.010
Of course. What's up?

24:20.113 --> 24:23.013
Carmen tells me you don't want
to go to her birthday party.

24:24.221 --> 24:25.705
Pa, it's not that
I don't want to.

24:25.809 --> 24:26.879
I just...

24:28.812 --> 24:30.365
I don't like how Margaret's
sticking her nose in it.

24:30.469 --> 24:32.574
Agreed.

24:32.678 --> 24:34.024
Pero es tu hermana.

24:34.127 --> 24:35.474
I want you there.

24:36.889 --> 24:38.373
Entiendo.

24:38.477 --> 24:40.962
And are you asking me
as my father,

24:41.031 --> 24:42.032
or as my boss?

24:42.135 --> 24:43.551
[chuckles]

24:43.654 --> 24:45.035
You're the CEO, V.

24:45.138 --> 24:47.347
Mm-hmm. You're still
Chairman of the Board.

24:47.451 --> 24:49.453
Carmen adores you.

24:50.903 --> 24:53.388
I just think if you don't go,
you're gonna regret it.

24:55.183 --> 24:56.667
This issue with Billy.

24:58.566 --> 24:59.705
Are you and Lettie okay?

25:02.017 --> 25:04.882
Well, I want us to be.

25:06.919 --> 25:09.231
But when you start
to lose trust...

25:11.406 --> 25:13.891
...what are you left with?

25:13.995 --> 25:21.071
♪♪

25:21.174 --> 25:28.216
♪♪

25:28.319 --> 25:35.361
♪♪

25:35.430 --> 25:42.610
♪♪

25:45.267 --> 25:46.683
[brakes screech,
engine shuts off]

26:16.298 --> 26:17.472
Wait.

26:17.576 --> 26:19.301
Lettie.

26:38.010 --> 26:39.839
[knock on door]

26:41.876 --> 26:44.016
[Spanish chatter
on television]

27:19.707 --> 27:20.846
[woman screams]

27:20.949 --> 27:22.157
Aah!

27:22.951 --> 27:24.159
Aah!

27:24.263 --> 27:26.368
♪♪

27:26.472 --> 27:27.438
[indistinct shouting]

27:27.507 --> 27:28.992
Vamonos. iVamonos!

27:29.061 --> 27:31.063
-[gunshot]
-[man speaks Spanish]

27:31.166 --> 27:32.616
[gunshot]

27:32.685 --> 27:33.824
-Aah!
-Aah!

27:33.893 --> 27:36.551
[shouting in Spanish]

27:36.655 --> 27:37.690
[both shout]

27:37.759 --> 27:39.278
[engine revs]

27:39.347 --> 27:40.831
[groans]

27:47.907 --> 27:50.289
[engine revs]

27:50.358 --> 27:55.294
♪♪

28:00.023 --> 28:09.066
♪♪

28:09.170 --> 28:18.213
♪♪

28:18.317 --> 28:27.360
♪♪

28:27.429 --> 28:36.507
♪♪

28:36.576 --> 28:37.716
[Reyna Tropical's "Mas Y Mas"
plays]

28:37.785 --> 28:40.166
♪ Por donde lo sigues mi amor♪

28:40.270 --> 28:41.409
♪ Si te brilla y te quita
el dolor♪

28:41.512 --> 28:45.413
♪♪

28:45.482 --> 28:47.898
♪ Por donde lo sigues mi amor♪

28:47.967 --> 28:49.969
♪ Si te brilla y te quita
el dolor♪

28:50.073 --> 28:53.697
I call it
"Veinte-Riquísimo."

28:53.766 --> 28:54.802
♪ Por donde lo sigues mi amor♪

28:54.905 --> 28:55.906
Margaret.

28:55.975 --> 28:57.943
How are you, my love?

28:59.151 --> 29:01.222
-Mwah.
-Mwah.

29:01.291 --> 29:03.465
I'm impressed.

29:03.569 --> 29:04.846
Inching your way closer to

29:04.950 --> 29:06.641
Carmen's 5%
of the company stock.

29:07.435 --> 29:09.609
-You look good, Antonio.
-Mm.

29:09.713 --> 29:11.128
And you're cynical,
so you must be eating.

29:11.197 --> 29:14.166
-[chuckles]
-[laughs]

29:14.269 --> 29:16.444
CARMEN: V! You came!

29:17.445 --> 29:19.930
-Oh, [speaks Spanish]
-iAy!

29:19.999 --> 29:23.865
-Subtle.
-Hey, I'm glad you're here.

29:23.969 --> 29:25.729
Me too.

29:25.798 --> 29:27.489
[gasps, chuckles]

29:27.593 --> 29:29.422
Margaret, hi.

29:29.491 --> 29:32.080
Veronica, sweetheart.

29:33.288 --> 29:35.394
I missed you so much.

29:37.603 --> 29:38.569
I'm only here for my sister.

29:38.638 --> 29:41.227
♪ Mas y mas♪

29:41.331 --> 29:42.263
♪ Que venga lo que tiene
que ver hoy♪

29:42.332 --> 29:44.127
You're still dead to me.

29:45.438 --> 29:47.578
I'll take what I can get,
darling.

29:47.647 --> 29:49.235
-Well, I'm glad V showed up.
-Mm-hmm.

29:49.339 --> 29:51.065
Now it's just Mateo
that's missing.

29:51.168 --> 29:52.860
Why is he such a lone wolf?

29:52.963 --> 29:55.794
Still early.
Maybe he's getting a mani-pedi.

29:55.863 --> 29:57.899
Ooh. I would pay to see that.

29:58.003 --> 29:59.004
[laughs]

29:59.073 --> 30:01.869
[vehicle approaches]

30:07.460 --> 30:08.841
[car door closes]

30:08.910 --> 30:11.188
I was gonna have
a quiet night,

30:11.257 --> 30:13.915
but Junior here convinced me
to come out and see your place.

30:14.019 --> 30:15.917
Did he, now?

30:16.021 --> 30:18.023
And he got Daniela
to drive you, too.

30:18.092 --> 30:20.611
You know, I can be
pretty persuasive.

30:20.680 --> 30:23.373
I volunteered.

30:23.476 --> 30:25.513
-Take a walk?
-Okay.

30:27.860 --> 30:30.311
What do you got here?

30:30.380 --> 30:34.418
Um...you know, 21 acres.

30:34.522 --> 30:36.696
All volcanic ash.
And I'm going old school.

30:36.765 --> 30:40.631
Dry farm, native yeast,
and space the vines.

30:40.700 --> 30:42.012
It's gonna bring
your yields down.

30:42.081 --> 30:43.876
Yeah, but the juice
will be magic.

30:43.945 --> 30:46.223
No doubt about that. Wow.

30:48.916 --> 30:50.227
[chuckles]

30:50.296 --> 30:53.265
Look, I'm sorry if
I freaked you out the other day.

30:53.368 --> 30:54.956
The reason I wanted you
to see this place

30:55.060 --> 30:58.546
is so you didn't think I needed
you to fill a hole or whatever.

30:58.649 --> 30:59.581
You know? I'm good.

30:59.685 --> 31:01.860
I can see that.

31:03.378 --> 31:05.311
You've come a long way from
that little boy I remember

31:05.415 --> 31:06.416
running through the vine rows

31:06.519 --> 31:07.900
and screaming
on that tire swing.

31:07.969 --> 31:09.833
[chuckling]
God, that swing.

31:09.902 --> 31:11.145
You couldn't keep me
off that thing.

31:11.248 --> 31:12.491
Except when I fell off.

31:12.560 --> 31:14.217
Broke my arm. You remember?

31:14.286 --> 31:16.219
You had to drive me
to the hospital.

31:16.288 --> 31:17.496
What was I? Like, 5?

31:17.565 --> 31:21.534
4. Only I didn't take you.

31:21.603 --> 31:23.571
I was wasted.

31:23.674 --> 31:26.608
I could barely stand.

31:26.712 --> 31:28.783
I lost my balance
and pushed you into the tree.

31:28.887 --> 31:30.889
That's how you broke you arm.

31:30.958 --> 31:32.752
And I didn't rush you
to the hospital.

31:32.856 --> 31:34.237
It was Joe.

31:34.306 --> 31:36.446
Wait, I'm sorry.

31:36.549 --> 31:38.482
He -- He never told me that.

31:38.586 --> 31:39.759
He just let me think
that it was you.

31:39.828 --> 31:42.901
Maybe Joe's not
the monster you think he is.

31:42.970 --> 31:46.180
Just like I'm not the man
you think you remember.

31:46.283 --> 31:50.563
Look, I don't care
what mistakes you made.

31:50.632 --> 31:51.979
The fact that you can own it
is enough.

31:52.082 --> 31:53.773
Everything else is gonna
take care of itself.

31:55.327 --> 31:57.122
God willing.

31:57.191 --> 32:01.022
Now, why don't you go take
that amazing young woman

32:01.126 --> 32:03.473
to your sister's
birthday party?

32:05.164 --> 32:06.717
[Aiza's "Sizzlin'" plays]

32:06.786 --> 32:08.581
♪ Oh na na ♪

32:08.650 --> 32:10.342
♪ I'm sizzlin' sizzlin' yeah ♪

32:10.445 --> 32:12.206
♪ Oh na na ♪

32:12.309 --> 32:13.932
♪ I'm sizzlin' sizzlin' yeah ♪

32:14.001 --> 32:15.899
♪ Oh na na ah ah ♪

32:15.968 --> 32:17.625
♪ I'm sizzlin' sizzlin' yeah ♪

32:17.728 --> 32:19.109
♪ Oh na na ♪

32:19.178 --> 32:22.354
♪ I'm sizzlin' sizzlin' yeah ♪

32:22.457 --> 32:25.184
[gasps] Mateo.

32:25.288 --> 32:26.979
[chuckles]

32:27.048 --> 32:28.670
-Wow.
-Happy birthday.

32:28.774 --> 32:30.741
You don't respond to texts
anymore or what?

32:30.810 --> 32:32.053
Mm.

32:32.157 --> 32:33.158
-Oh.
-Hey, hey.

32:33.227 --> 32:35.954
-[laughs]
-Okay.

32:38.163 --> 32:39.233
How'd you get
this gorgeous creature

32:39.336 --> 32:40.475
to agree
to come with you, huh?

32:40.579 --> 32:41.787
Aww.

32:41.856 --> 32:47.344
♪♪

32:47.413 --> 32:48.863
Reminds me of our wedding.

32:48.967 --> 32:50.692
[chuckles]

32:50.796 --> 32:53.005
Minus my father
drinking himself silly.

32:53.074 --> 32:54.317
And scowling at us.

32:54.386 --> 32:57.044
[sighs]
His trademark expression.

32:57.147 --> 32:59.322
[Sade's "Your Love Is King"
playing]

32:59.391 --> 33:08.089
♪♪

33:08.193 --> 33:09.677
What do you say?

33:09.746 --> 33:11.713
You're trying to
take over my company.

33:11.817 --> 33:13.853
We're in a state of
an all-out war.

33:17.098 --> 33:18.997
It's all part
of the dance.

